dct_title_s: Map of the discoveries in Australia : copied from the latest M.S. Surveys in the Colonial Office
dct_description_sm: Map of Southeastern Australia showing explorers routes for the period 1817-1830 and the nineteen counties in New South Wales. Relief shown by hachures.; Includes referenced table entitled: Reference to the tracks of the travellers and the number of miles explored by each.; At bottom right of sheet: 35.
dct_publisher_sm: Pubd. by J. Arrowsmith,  33 East St. Red Lion Square (London)
